Are you looking in the right place?  The crawl.log has an entry per 
downloaded URL.  There is nothing related to telegraaf.nl, assuming 
thats the site you are crawling?  If not, what are you crawling? (Former 
is a rhetorical question)

I do not know much about the MirrorWriter.  We don&#39;t use it hereabouts.  
Reading through the code, the mirrorwriter does its best to create 
unique names on disk out of a page&#39;s URI.  I&#39;m guessing its responsible 
for the rewriting of the &#39;r=NUMBER&#39; parameter inserting it before the 
&#39;.html&#39; (Can you find reference to the numbers in your crawl.log?  Or, 
if you look at the site you are crawling w/ your browser, is it offering 
pages with a &#39;r=NUMBER&#39; parameter?).   In the mirrorwriter, you can ask 
it to write the URL suffix on the end when creating names on disk.  Do 
you have this enabled?   Also, its odd that there is not a directory per 
host crawled (Default settings will do this).

